This is a IIB supergravity solution with four supercharges.  There are no obvious causality violating regions in this geometry, so it may appear as though the full ten dimensional geometry has resolved the causal problems associated with the black hole.  This conclusion, however, is misleading.  To see this explicitly, consider space-like curves which have tangent vectors given by l^  _  =  _z  + (__1  -  __2 ) .
